<h2>7.2 WIA Talk Integration</h2>

<h3>7.2.1 Overview</h3>

<p>WIA Talk is the text-to-speech standard that converts AAC text output to natural-sounding speech. It supports multiple languages, voices, and speech parameters.</p>

<h3>7.2.2 Integration API</h3>

<pre>
import { WiaAAC } from 'wia-aac';
import { WiaTalk } from 'wia-talk';

// Initialize both systems
const aac = new WiaAAC();
const talk = new WiaTalk({
    voice: 'en-US-Neural-J',
    rate: 1.0,
    pitch: 1.0
});

// Connect AAC to Talk
aac.on('text', async (text) =&gt; {
    await talk.speak(text);
});

// Advanced usage with SSML
aac.on('text', async (text, context) =&gt; {
    const ssml = talk.buildSSML(text, {
        emphasis: context.emphasis,
        pauseAfter: context.punctuation ? 300 : 0
    });
    await talk.speakSSML(ssml);
});
</pre>

<h3>7.2.3 Voice Configuration</h3>

<pre>
WIA Talk Voice Options:

Languages Supported:
  - English (US, UK, AU, IN)
  - Korean
  - Japanese
  - Chinese (Mandarin, Cantonese)
  - Spanish
  - French
  - German
  - And 50+ more languages

Voice Types:
  - Neural (high quality, natural)
  - Standard (lower latency)
  - Custom (user-trained)

Configuration Example:
{
    "voice": {
        "id": "en-US-Neural-J",
        "language": "en-US",
        "gender": "male",
        "age": "adult"
    },
    "parameters": {
        "rate": 1.0,        // 0.5 - 2.0
        "pitch": 1.0,       // 0.5 - 2.0
        "volume": 1.0,      // 0.0 - 1.0
        "emphasis": "moderate"
