<h2>7.5 Unified Output Manager</h2>

<h3>7.5.1 Overview</h3>

<p>The Output Manager coordinates all output modalities, ensuring synchronized delivery to speech, sign, and braille simultaneously.</p>

<h3>7.5.2 Implementation</h3>

<pre>
import { WiaAAC } from 'wia-aac';
import { OutputManager } from 'wia-aac/output';

const aac = new WiaAAC();
const output = new OutputManager();

// Configure outputs
output.configure({
    talk: {
        enabled: true,
        voice: 'en-US-Neural-J'
    },
    isp: {
        enabled: true,
        language: 'ASL',
        avatar: 'standard-human'
    },
    braille: {
        enabled: true,
        code: 'UEB',
        display: 'auto-detect'
    }
});

// Connect AAC to unified output
aac.on('text', async (text) =&gt; {
    await output.broadcast(text);
    // Automatically sends to all enabled outputs
});

// Output events
output.on('talkComplete', () =&gt; console.log('Speech done'));
output.on('ispComplete', () =&gt; console.log('Sign animation done'));
output.on('brailleComplete', () =&gt; console.log('Braille displayed'));

// Error handling
output.on('outputError', (error, modality) =&gt; {
    console.error(`${modality} error:`, error);
    // Continue with other outputs
});
</pre>

<h3>7.5.3 Synchronization</h3>

<pre>
Output Synchronization Options:

Mode 1: Simultaneous (Default)
  - All outputs start together
  - Best for live communication

Mode 2: Sequential
  - Speech first, then sign, then braille
  - For presentation/teaching

Mode 3: Priority
  - Primary output immediately
  - Others as resources allow

Configuration:
{
    "synchronization": {
        "mode": "simultaneous",
        "startDelay": 0,
        "outputs": {
            "talk": { "priority": 1 },
            "isp": { "priority": 2 },
            "braille": { "priority": 3 }
        }
    },
    "fallback": {
        "onError": "continue",  // continue | stop | retry
        "retryCount": 2
    }
}
</pre>

